						               													<description>Magnomania was developed and produced for Magnus Management Consultancy (since 2009 called Eurogroup Consulting) by Identity Games International B.V., Rotterdam, the Netherlands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the front of the manual:&amp;#10;It's amazing what you can accomplish if you don't mind who gets the credit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the back of the manual:&amp;#10;Magnomania (some higlights):&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     You are an entrepreneur for Magnus&amp;#10;     Establish your consultants in as many countries as possible&amp;#10;     Try to get 'In Business' with your projects&amp;#10;     Plan your strategy and make smart choices&amp;#10;     Collect the points you need to win Magnomania&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the first page of the rules:&amp;#10;In this game you'll take part in Magnus' worldwide expansion.&amp;#10;Are you the sharpest entrepreneur? Will you be the first one to achieve your goal?&amp;#10;Consider your investment decisions carefully, execute takeovers, and make sure you get the biggest share of the market.&amp;#10;Play Magnomania, plan, decide, and win!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Quick game overview:&amp;#10;As a player of Magnomania, you are a Magnus entrepreneur. You travel as an entrepreneur around the gameboard and try to be the first to earn the required number of points in order win. You earn points by taking the biggest market share on a given continent and being 'In Business' internationally. As soon as an entrepreneur (pawn) arrives in a country he can begin a consultancy project. You indicate the stages of your project by a consultant (disc). When a project is completed, you as the entrepreneur are 'In Business' in that country.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
